ry, 2026;\n originally announced January 2026.\n\n- From Individual Prompts to Collective Intelligence: Mainstreaming Generative AI in the Classroom\n\n Abstract:\n\n Engineering classrooms are increasingly experimenting with generative AI (GenAI), but most uses remain confined to individual prompting and isolated assistance. This narrow framing risks reinforcing equity gaps and only rewarding the already privileged or motivated students. We argue instead for a shift toward collective intelligence (CI)-focused pedagogy, w…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 7 January, 2026;\n originally announced January 2026.\n\n- Multimodal Spatial Reasoning in the Large Model Era: A Survey and Benchmarks\n\n Authors:\n\n [Xu Zheng](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zheng%2C+X),\n\n [Zihao Dongfang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Dongfang%2C+Z),\n\n [Lutao Jiang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Jiang%2C+L),\n\n [Boyuan Zheng](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zheng%2C+B),\n\n [Yulong Guo](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Guo%2C+Y),\n\n [Zhenquan Zhang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zhang%2C+Z),\n\n [Giuliano Albanese](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Albanese%2C+G),\n\n [Runyi Yang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Yang%2C+R),\n\n [Mengjiao Ma](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Ma%2C+M),\n\n [Zixin Zhang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zhang%2C+Z),\n\n [Chenfei Liao](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Liao%2C+C),\n\n [Dingcheng Zhen](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zhen%2C+D),\n\n [Yuanhuiyi Lyu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Lyu%2C+Y),\n\n [Yuqian Fu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Fu%2C+Y),\n\n [Bin Ren](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Ren%2C+B),\n\n [Linfeng Zhang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zhang%2C+L),\n\n [Danda Pani Paudel](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Paudel%2C+D+P),\n\n [Nicu Sebe](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Sebe%2C+N),\n\n [Luc Van Gool](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Van+Gool%2C+L),\n\n [Xuming Hu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Hu%2C+X)\n\n Abstract:\n\n …and reason, showing promising performance across diverse spatial tasks. However, systematic reviews and publicly available benchmarks for these models remain limited. In this survey, we provide a comprehensive review of multimodal spatial reasoning tasks with large models, categorizing recent progress in multimodal large language models (MLLMs) and introduci…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 2 November, 2025; v1 submitted 29 October, 2025;\n originally announced October 2025.\n\n- A Comprehensive Survey on World Models for Embodied AI\n\n Authors:\n\n [Xinqing Li](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Li%2C+X),\n\n [Xin He](/search/?searchtype=author&query=He%2C+X),\n\n [Le Zhang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zhang%2C+L),\n\n [Min Wu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Wu%2C+M),\n\n [Xiaoli Li](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Li%2C+X),\n\n [Yun Liu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Liu%2C+Y)\n\n Abstract:\n\n Embodied…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 29 November, 2025; v1 submitted 19 October, 2025;\n originally announced October 2025.\n\n- Beyond Pipelines: A Survey of the Paradigm Shift toward Model-Native Agentic AI\n\n Authors:\n\n [Jitao Sang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Sang%2C+J),\n\n [Jinlin Xiao](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Xiao%2C+J),\n\n [Jiarun Han](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Han%2C+J),\n\n [Jilin Chen](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Chen%2C+J),\n\n [Xiaoyi Chen](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Chen%2C+X),\n\n [Shuyu Wei](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Wei%2C+S),\n\n [Yongjie Sun](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Sun%2C+Y),\n\n [Yuhang Wang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Wang%2C+Y)\n\n Abstract:\n\n The rapid evolution of agentic AI marks a new phase in artificial intelligence, where Large Language Models (LLMs) no longer merely respond but act, reason, and adapt. This…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 26 October, 2025; v1 submitted 19 October, 2025;\n originally announced October 2025.\n\n- Aligning Perception, Reasoning, Modeling and Interaction: A Surve