t Visuomotor Prediction for Vision-Language-Action Model\n\n Authors:\n\n [Xiaoxu Xu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Xu%2C+X),\n\n [Hao Li](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Li%2C+H),\n\n [Jinhui Ye](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Ye%2C+J),\n\n [Yilun Chen](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Chen%2C+Y),\n\n [Jia Zeng](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Zeng%2C+J),\n\n [Xinyi Chen](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Chen%2C+X),\n\n [Linning Xu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Xu%2C+L),\n\n [Dahua Lin](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Lin%2C+D),\n\n [Weixin Li](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Li%2C+W),\n\n [Jiangmiao Pang](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Pang%2C+J)\n\n Abstract:\n\n Predictive foresight is important to intelligent embodied agents. Since the motor execution of a…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 11 March, 2026;\n originally announced March 2026.\n\n- Observing and Controlling Features in Vision-Language-Action Models\n\n Authors:\n\n [Hugo Buurmeijer](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Buurmeijer%2C+H),\n\n [Carmen Amo Alonso](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Alonso%2C+C+A),\n\n [Aiden Swann](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Swann%2C+A),\n\n [Marco Pavone](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Pavone%2C+M)\n\n Abstract:\n\n Vision-Language-Action Models (VLAs) have shown remarkable progress towards…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 5 March, 2026;\n originally announced March 2026.\n\n- Cognition to Control - Multi-Agent Learning for Human-Humanoid Collaborative Transport\n\n Abstract:\n\n Effective human-robot collaboration (HRC) requires translating high-level intent into contact-stable whole-body motion while continuously adapting to a human partner. Many vision-language-action (…\n ▽ More\n\n Submitted 4 March, 2026;\n originally announced March 2026.\n\n- Latent Reasoning VLA: Latent Thinking and Prediction for Vision-Language-Action Models\n\n Authors:\n\n [Shuanghao Bai](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Bai%2C+S),\n\n [Jing Lyu](/search/?searchtype=author&query=Lyu%2C+J),\